ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, metal-free doped CDs with superior antimicrobial properties were prepared through one-pot hydrothermal approach taking m-aminophenol as precursor and introducing phosphoric acid doping modulation (Scheme 1
                     ). Developed P-doping CDs, i.e., P-CDs, showed superior oxidase-like activity under light irradiation, and the maximum reaction rate (Vmax) of superoxide radicals (O2
                     •−) gengrated from oxygen activation was 33.3 × 10−8 M/s with a Michaelis constant (Km) of 0.71 mM. Through evaluations based on plate counts, growth curves, bacterial staining and scanning electron microscopy (SEM), an exciting antimicrobial performance against coli (E. coli) and S. aureus under a white LED irridation was obtained. Elaborated XRD, Raman, and TEM investigations on our P-CDs, in this study, will not only contribute to the development of new materials for inhibit bacterial contamination but also provide a new strategy for P-doping to promote the catalytic activity of CDs.
